  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You designate a single creature other than the target, which will become the subject's 'nemesis'. In the subject's experience, nothing they do against their nemesis seems effective, crushing their morale. Each time the subject takes an offensive action against its nemesis, it suffers a cumulative -1 morale penalty to skill checks, ability checks and attack rolls made against the nemesis (up to -10 total). Even if the action was successful, the subject believes its nemesis was completely unaffected.<br><br>In addition, each time this happens the subject must make a Will save to avoid suffering non-lethal damage equal to the damage the offensive action dealt or would have dealt (halved if using cumulative non-lethal damage rules, minimum 1).<br><br>This technique can be dispelled. When the illusion ends, the penalty incurred as well as any nonlethal damage dealt disappear.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
